Turkish Current Account Gap Widened to $5.9 Billion in January, Bank Says

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-03-11T08:01:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/turkish-current-account-gap-widened-to-5-9-billion-in-january-bank-says.html
  Turkey ’s current-account deficit
almost doubled in January from a year earlier, the 13th
consecutive widening in a measure Moody’s Investor Services says
is a “key risk.”  The deficit rose to $5.9 billion from $3.1 billion in the
same month of 2010, the central bank in Ankara said on its
website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
